<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Typhoon Landed in East China's Coastal Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A strong typhoon codenamed
Number 11, or Typhoon Winnie as it was called before reaching east
China's Zhejiang province, landed at Wenling City at 21:30 hours
(Beijing Time) today, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The local people are now making every effort to combat the
typhoon, along with thunderstorm and tidal waves.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China, and Chinese Premier Li Peng extended
their cordial regards to locals right after the landing and
required leading officials at all levels and people to combat the
typhoon and involve themselves in the relief work to reduce the
losses to the minimum.
</P>
<P>
Latest weather forecast indicated the typhoon would further
move northwesternward and affected such cities as Shaoxing, Jinhua
and Hangzhou. By the 19:30 hours, locals from the coastal regions
of these cities have all moved to safer places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
