<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Traffic Collision in Arizona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 18 (Xinhua) Eight people, including five
children, were killed and at least five others seriously injured
when a speeding sedan ran struck a Dodge minivan Sunday night in
Tucson, Arizona.
</P>
<P>
Seven people died at the scene and one died early today at the
hospital. The children killed in the accident ranged from 3 years
old into their teens, local media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Five other people were taken to area hospitals with serious
injuries, including the suspected driver of the sedan.
</P>
<P>
The van contained a family who appeared to be returning home
from a church function. At least seven of the victims were riding
in the van.
</P>
<P>
Police said alcohol or drugs may be involved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
