<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taliban Claim Arrest of Rival Warlord's Close Aide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban Islamic
militia today claimed that they have arrested a close aide to
Afghanistan's former military chief Ahmad Masood, Afghan sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban forces have arrested Abdul Baqi who is said to be
Masood's close aide in the northern Kunduz province controlled by
the militia, said the Afghan sources in Peshawar, a major city in
northwestern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Baqi was distributing money among local people to instigate
them to revolt against the Islamic militia until he was arrested
by the patrolling Taliban men, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
But the sources did not disclose the specific location where
Baqi was caught.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban's such claim has not been independently confirmed
so far.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few weeks, the forces loyal to Masood and the
Taliban fighters have been engaged in fierce fighting north of
Kabul. But both sides have failed to make any significant
territorial gains.  
</P>
</TEXT>
