<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strasbourg Registers High Ozone Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The French city Strasbourg today
registered a new high level of ozone pollution with 226
micro-grams of ozone per cubic meters in its central Kleber
Square, announced the official Agency for Supervision and Study of
Atmospheric Pollution in Alsace.
</P>
<P>
The worst polluted area is in the central area of Strasbourg,
followed by its suburbs, while other parts of the Alsace region in
which Strasbourg is located have lower levels of pollution.
</P>
<P>
Both Paris and Strasbourg last week attained the level-two of
ozone pollution, with more than 181 micro-grams of ozone per cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
Waste air from cars, high temperatures, sunshine and lack of
wind are the main factors for the rise of pollution level in both
Strasbourg and Paris.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Upper Rhine and Lower Rhine, which make up
the Alsace region, have called on the local residents to use
automobiles only for the purposes of strict necessity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
