<HEADLINE> EU Envoy Meets Arafat on Israeli-Palestinian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 18 (Xinhua) -- European Union's Mideast envoy
Miguel Moratinos met with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat in Gaza
today on the Israeli-Palestinian crisis, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The talks focused on the restricting measures by the Israeli
government against the Palestinians following the July 30 suicide
bombings in west Jerusalem which killed 16 people.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government barred tens of thousands of Palestinians
from working in Israel and stopped transferring funds owed the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) to pressure the authority to
crack down on terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos said that he expected Israel to release the frozen
funds as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the current security cooperation between Israel
and the PNA, Moratinos said that the meeting Sunday night between
Israeli, Palestinian and U.S. security officials in Ramallah went
well and "Israelis are now more satisfied with security matters."
</P>
<P>
At the Ramallah meeting, the Israelis secured Palestinians'
promise of security cooperation while the Palestinians asked
Israel to drop the punitive measures. 
