<HEADLINE> UNDP, Botswana Fight Against AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Botswana had launched two
new projects costing a total of 6.4 million dollars to slow the
spread of HIV and AIDS with help of the United Nations Development
Program (UNDP).
</P>
<P>
UNDP Flash reported today that the first project would enhance
government capacity to undertake national and local initiatives
against the epidemic. New research on the incidence and causes of
the disease's spread would be carried out, people with AIDS would
get more help from local government and non-governmental
organizations supporting HIV-infected people would be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The second project, built on the first, would be aimed at
preventing infection among women, and offering special assistance
to those who already have the disease. 
