<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Six Lebanese civilians were
killed and 28 others seriously injured today in shelling by the
Israeli troops and its allied militiamen, the South Lebanon
Army (SLA), the official Lebanese News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead were a one-month-old girl, a six-year-old boy
and a woman, and most of the injured are in serious conditions.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Israeli troops and SLA army today fired six
bombs at southern Lebanese city of Saida, about 40 Kilometers
south of Beirut.
</P>
<P>
The attack, which started at 2:25 pm (11:25 GMT) and lasted
until 3:20 pm, is the first time for this port city over the past
years.
</P>
<P>
Israeli radio quoted one Israeli security official as saying
that the attack was launched by SLA, not Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
He added that this is a retaliatory action for the death of two
children, whose father was reportedly one of the SLA's leaders.
</P>
<P>
In the morning, the car carrying the two children was exploded
by the mines on a road in the southern province of Jezzine, a
strip of land officially outside the Israeli-occupied zone but
under the SLA control.
</P>
<P>
But, the Hezbullah, or Party of God, said the two civilians
were killed by the Israeli troops and urged Lebanese government to
take responsibility to protect its citizens from the terrorism
inside the occupied zone as well as outside. 
</P>
