<HEADLINE> Swaziland Urged to Prevent Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The National Disaster
Committee of Swaziland today called for an emergency meeting to
discuss measures to take predictions of another drought in the
coming agricultural season.
</P>
<P>
Local press quoted the committee chairman, Ben Nsibandze, as
saying that the meeting is to consider what steps to take and
advise the government on the predicament.
</P>
<P>
Forecasts of El Nino winds, usually associated with drought
conditions in southern Africa, have caused uneasiness in the
region recovering from yet another near-famine five years ago.
</P>
<P>
During the 1992 drought in the country, the committee had to
seek external assistance for food to avoid starvation.
</P>
<P>
The drought left more than 90,000 cattle dead in Swaziland,
while southern Africa as a whole was forced to import tens of
thousands of tons of grain. 
</P>
