stands inside the market to come and trade outside, where there
is more business.
</P>
<P>
Mulenga said the problem of vendors surrounding the new market
with 3,000 stalls will be dealt with once and for all, adding
that if they are left to continue their trade, the purpose of
building the expensive market will be defeated.
</P>
<P>
Numerous street vendors do theie business in Lusaka's downtown
centres because of inadequate of market places. The city market
was opened last week part of the government efforts to solve
the problem. 
