forces loyal to President Lissouba tried to disarm the "Cobra"
militia of former president Sassou Nguesso. Continuous fighting
has killed some 3,000 people over the past two months.
</P>
<P>
The international community has made efforts to broker
ceasefire in Brazzaville, capital of the Congo Republic, but two
ceasefire agreements reached by two the sides since the crisis
broke out have been violated respectively.  
