<HEADLINE> First Silk Pictorial Published in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Museums and collectors can now
add to their showcases a silk newspaper featuring 31 color photos
of the world's gala Hong Kong handover festivities on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The special edition of China News Pictorial, published on July
4, candidly depicts the festivals and worldwide celebrations for
marking China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou Kaidi Silk Company, located in eastern coastal
Zhejiang Province, printed 2,000 copies of the newspaper on silk.
</P>
<P>
Veteran collectors said that the exquisitely-printed photos
have a high value of collection.
</P>
<P>
China News Pictorial, owned by Xinhua News Agency, is the sole
weekly photo-oriented newspaper in China. The Pictorial will
auction off 30 limited edition copies.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the Party Literature Research Center of
the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, Central
Archives, the Museum of the Chinese Revolution and other museums,
together with 150 collectors attended a publication party today in
Beijing for the unveiling of the silk paper. 
</P>
