<HEADLINE> Syrian Newspapers Denounce Israeli Massacre in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Syrian newspapers denounced
today the massacre committed by Israeli forces in the Lebanese
port city of Sidon.
</P>
<P>
Israeli forces, together with the pro-Israeli South Lebanon
Army (SLA), shelled Monday the Lebanese port city of Sidon
inhabited by 200,000 Lebanese, killing nine people and wounding 43
others.
</P>
<P>
"This massacre indicates that Israel has adopted a strategy to
push the region into further catastrophes," Syrian newspaper
Teshreen said today.
</P>
<P>
The paper added that Israel, under the Netanyahu government
would not hesitate to commit all sorts of crimes.
</P>
<P>
Al-Baath, mouthpiece of the Syrian ruling party Arab Baath
Socialist Party, pointed out today that the new Israeli massacre
is not remote from the Qana massacre on April 18, 1996 when
Israeli forces shelled a camp of the U.N. peace-keeping forces in
south Lebanon, killing about 110 Lebanese civilians and wounding
150 others in addition to 15 soldiers belonging to the
U.N. peace-keeping forces.
</P>
<P>
Newspaper Al-thawrah today called on the U.S. Administration to
exercise its political and moral responsibilities by reminding
Netanyahu and other Israeli extremists that it is impossible to
combine peace with occupation, and that the establishment of peace
does primarily require abiding by the principle of complete
withdrawal from occupied Arab territories and returning land and
rights to their legitimate owners. 
</P>
