<HEADLINE> Hang Seng Bank Opens First Branch in New Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng Bank, the
second-largest locally-incorporated bank in Hong Kong, has
extended its service to Tseung Kwan O, the fast-growing new town,
by opening its 147th Hong Kong branch in the town's Metro City
today.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Edgar Cheng, vice chairman of the bank and Mr. Alexander S
K Au, vice chairman and chief executive of the bank, officiated at
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Tseung Kwan O, currently with a population of about 170,000,
has developed into a major new town, Au said. "When the Mass
Transit Railway extension to Tseung Kwan O is completed, this
district will become a fully-developed residential and commercial
hub and offer greater business potential."
</P>
<P>
The opening of the Metro City Branch, Hang Seng's first branch
in the new town, is in line with the bank's strategy to establish
a presence in the newly-developed districts, he said.
</P>
<P>
Occupying a floor area of about 186 square meters, the branch
offers a wide range of services including deposit-taking, loans,
remittances and personal financial services.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1933, Hang Seng Bank, a principal member of the HSBC
Group, now employs a staff of over 8,000 in its 147 local
branches, its Guangzhou branch and representative offices in
Shanghai, Shenzhen and Xiamen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
