<HEADLINE> Floods Kill Four in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Flash floods brought about by
monsoon rains have claimed at least four lives and rendered
thousands of others homeless in the northern and central
Philippines, local television reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The four confirmed fatalities included two drowned, one crushed
in a landslide, and one electrocuted when walking along a flooded
street, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the National Disaster Coordination Council said more
than 3,000 families or 19,000 persons were severely affected by
the floods and some of them have been evacuated to safer places.
</P>
<P>
The National Red Cross said in a bulletin that it had already
provided emergency food supplies to at least 897 families or 5,119
persons in various parts of Metro Manila and northwestern Luzon.
</P>
<P>
The massive floods also led to the suspension of school classes
as well as government offices in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
The floods were caused by torrential monsoon rains which began
to slash the country Sunday afternoon and were intensified by
typhoon Winnie.  
</P>
</TEXT>
