<HEADLINE> National Day Celebrations To Be Staged in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will, on October 1,
celebrate the first National Day since it became a Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of China on July 1, the Government
Information Services Office announced today.
</P>
<P>
The Home Affairs Bureau has been tasked with coordinating a
program of celebration activities on that day.
</P>
<P>
At 8 a.m., the National Flag will be raised at a simple and
solemn ceremony to be held at the sea front promenade of the Hong
Kong Convention and Exhibition Center (HKCEC), near the statue of
the Gold Bauhinia which was a gift from the Central People's
Government to mark Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa will host a reception at the
Grand Hall of the HKCEC Extension in the late afternoon. Some
5,000 guests from all sectors of the community are expected to
attend the reception.
</P>
<P>
The two provisional municipal councils will organize recreation
and sports activities in Victoria Park, Sha Tin and Tsuen Wan in
the afternoon to celebrate the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a full program of celebration activities will be
sponsored by Hong Kong's 18 Provisional District Boards at
district level. The Home Affairs Department is applying for funds
to enable the boards to meet some of the costs of the district
activities.
</P>
<P>
A cultural performance organized by the Association of
Compatriots in Hong Kong for Celebration of the National Day of
the People's Republic of China will take place at Hong Kong
Coliseum from 7 to 9 p.m..
</P>
<P>
To round off the evening, the Association of Hong Kong
Guangdong Community Organizations for Celebration of Return of
Hong Kong to China is planning to stage a 30-minute fireworks
display at Victoria Harbor at around 9:30 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
