<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Province to Hold Symposium on Foreign Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province is
expected to hold a two-day symposium to facilitate its economic
cooperation with investors from overseas, a provincial official
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The Anhui '97 (Beijing) Foreign Economic Cooperation Symposium"
will be held at the Chinese International Trade Center in Beijing
from August 28 to 29.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Ping, deputy governor of Anhui Province, said his
province expects to seek 4.5 billion US dollars worth of overseas
investment for its 143 major projects listed in the upcoming
symposium. The projects, to involve a total investment of 9.35
billion US dollars, will be focused mainly on infrastructures,
agricultural development and industrial technological improvement.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Province attaches great importance to the absorbing of
investment in various forms from major international financial
groups and transnational corporations as well as medium-sized and
small enterprises, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Scores of the world-renowned businesses, financial groups,
commercial counsellors and investment promotion units in China are
expected to attend the symposium, which is aimed at a deeper
understanding and long-term cooperation between Anhui and overseas
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials at the symposium will give an account of
Anhui's investment environment, major cooperative projects and
development zones, in addition to energy, transportation and
infrastructure development and policies concerning the inflow of
capital.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up some 3,750 overseas-funded projects,
with a contractual volume of 3.7 billion US dollars by the end of
last year, and 1.73 billion US dollars had actually been put to
use.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 countries and regions have come to invest in
Anhui, and a growing number of projects involve over 10 million US
dollars each in investment.
</P>
<P>
The scope of investment has been extended from the fields of
traditional electronics, machine building and chemical industries
to service trade and basic industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
