<HEADLINE> Agreement Signed for Phone Services at HK New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Airport Authority (AA)
signed today the license agreement for the provision of pay phone
and courtesy phone services in the passenger terminal building at
the new airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
New World Telephone (NWT), a major supplier of telecom services
in Hong Kong, was awarded a five-year license to provide a minimum
of 335 multi-media pay phones, 20 conventional-type pay phones, 45
courtesy phones, as well as 10 phone card vending machines.
</P>
<P>
NWT will also offer a variety of telephone services, including
local and international voice, fax and data calls; coin, calling
card and credit card payment; electronic Yellow Pages and other
directories; and Internet access.
</P>
<P>
"The award of this license will ensure that the traveling
public will have its communications needs amply catered for," said
AA Chief Executive Officer Dr. Henry Townsend. "This is yet
another feature that will make the terminal one of the best
passenger facilities in the world."
</P>
<P>
The new airport, replacing the now congested Kai Tak Airport,
is expected to be put into operation in April 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
