<HEADLINE> Key Car Project Passes State Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 19 (Xinhua) -- One of China's key state-owned
car projects with a designed annual production capacity of 150,000
units passed the state appraisal here today.
</P>
<P>
The car joint venture, clinched between China's First Auto
Works Corporation (FAW) and German-based Volkswagen AG, today also
turned out its 100,000 Jetta cars.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China and vice premier of the
State Council, the cabinet, attended a ceremony today in
Changchun, China's largest auto manufacturing city.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Peiyan, vice minister of the State Planning Commission,
led a state appraisal committee to review the project and
delivered the appraisal certificate to the venture this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Designated as one of the leading state projects in the Eighth
Five-year Plan (1991-1995), the work was jointly funded by the two
sides with 8.9 billion yuan, of which FAW held 60 percent of the
stake.
</P>
<P>
With full range of the facilities of a modern car enterprise,
including a car production plant and six workshops, the venture is
now capable of making 150,000 complete vehicles, 270,000 engines
and 180,000 transmissions per year.
</P>
<P>
The local content ratio of its Jetta car had reached 84 percent
by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, the venture earned 45
million yuan of profit and registered record-high production and
sales figures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
