<HEADLINE> Arab League Condemns Israeli Shelling in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdel Meguid today denounced the "Israeli massacre" in
southern Lebanon Monday claiming lives of innocent civilians.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here today, Meguid said that the
"continued Israeli aggression on Lebanon's sovereignty, territorial
integrity and security" will not deter the Lebanese people from
resisting Israel's occupation of the south.
</P>
<P>
"Resisting occupation is a legitimate action acknowledged by
the international law and human rights declaration," according to
the league's chief.
</P>
<P>
Meguid urged the international community, including the U.N.
Security Council, the EU and the co-sponsors of the peace process,
to move immediately to denounce Israel's attack and force it to
implement U.N. Resolution 425 which demands the withdrawal of Israeli
troops from southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, The Lebanese government today lodged
an urgent complaint with the International Committee Monitoring
the Ceasefire of the April Understanding, denouncing Israel's
violation of the understanding when it shelled civilian targets in
broad daylight Monday, away from military installations.
</P>
<P>
Six civilians were killed and 36 wounded in fierce shelling
Monday in the bloodiest attack on the southern port city of Sidon
since the end of a major Israeli offensive in south Lebanon in
April 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army said the pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army (SLA)
in the occupation zone, not Israeli troops, were behind the
attacks.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 Israeli troops have held a border occupation in a
self-declared "security zone" in south Lebanon since 1985, in
defiance of U.N. resolutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
