and general manager of the Bank of China Shanghai Branch, will be
transferred to Hong Kong to become Senior Deputy Chief Executive
responsible for the daily management of the Hong Kong-Macao
Regional Office, and concurrently as General Manager of the Hong
Kong Branch.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the bank said, Yang Zilin was
appointed by the head office to start working in Hong Kong in the
spring of 1994. During this period of more than three years, he
has "prudently and conscientiously" implemented the development
strategy of the Bank for the Hong Kong and Macao region.
</P>
<P>
The bank expressed the confidence that "the newly appointed
management team will, as always, fulfil the objectives of the
head office to work toward the continuing prosperity and stability
of the Hong Kong and Macao region, cooperate with the financial
sector and the community at large to further solidify and enhance
Hong Kong's status as an international financial center."
