<HEADLINE> International Electronics, Telecom Products Show Opens in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 19 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The 1997 Dalian
International Electronics and Telecom Products Exposition opened
today in this coastal city in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Sponsors of the five-day showcase event are the China Council
for the Promotion of International Trade, the local city
government, the Hong Kong Trade Development Council, and related
organizations from Japan and the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
Nearly 300 domestic and overseas manufacturers will participate
in the exhibition, which covers a floor space of 12,000 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
Overseas big-name companies attending include the Motorola of
the United States, Ericsson of Sweden, Siemens of Germany, Japan's
NTT, Panasonic and Mitsubishi and the ROK's Hyundai.
</P>
<P>
Trade talks and technical exchanges will be held during the
event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
