<HEADLINE> Over 50 Rebels killed In North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 Tamil rebels were killed
and many others injured today in a confrontation with government
troops in Northern Province of the country, according to military
spokesman here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the troops supported by armor, artillery and
air commenced advancing northward this morning from the earlier
held positions south of Puliyankulam town which is about 200
kilometers north of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
By about 10 am the advancing troops were confronted by a large
group of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels from
their prepared defenses.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with artillery, air and battle tanks,
inflicting heavy casualties among the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said more than 50 rebels were killed and a large
number injured while 7 soldiers were killed during the
confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The troops are going to attack on Puliyankulam town, the
spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging for a 14-year war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
