<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Train derailed, Injuring 3 in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 19 (Xinhua) -- An inter-urban train from
Yaounde en-route to Douala derailed Sunday close to Binguele
station, some 30 kilometers from Yaounde, Cameroun Tribune
reported today.
</P>
<P>
All passengers survived the accident but three people, the
driver and his assistant, and one passenger were wounded.
</P>
<P>
They were sent to the national social insurance fund hospital
in Yaounde, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Cameroun's Transport Minister Jean Bokam went to the area
where the accident occurred to assess the damage.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 12:15 a.m. Sunday, when the
engine-bearing cabin suddenly skidded off the rail, bringing the
journey to Douala, the economic center of the country, to an
abrupt halt, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the railway corporation said it is difficult to
figure out the cause of the accident now and they claimed that
this would be resolved when a team of engineers return after
probe from the area.
</P>
<P>
Four hours after the accident, the railway line, the busiest
in the country especially for goods, was reopened.
</P>
<P>
Passengers on the derailed train continued their journey to
Douala on another train after engineers working throughout the
night cleared the coaches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
