<HEADLINE> Albania Appoints New Chief of the General Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Albania's Chief of the General
Staff Adem Copani was dismissed from his post on Monday and
replaced by 45-year old Aleks Andoni, the local media reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The personnel change came as a result of a special order from
President and Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces, Rexhep
Meidani, who also promoted Andoni from a lieutenant colonel to a
brigadier general, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Andoni, with a doctor's degree in military science, worked at a
naval military base for 15 years before becoming an instructor and
later, president of a military academy.
</P>
<P>
The newly-formed Albanian government has already discharged 25
senior military officials in a bid to rebuild the army, which
nearly collapsed due to the country's political and economic
crisis early this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
