<HEADLINE> Chinese Tibetan Artists Perform in Palais des Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The brilliant performance by a
group of Chinese Tibetan artists here in the Palais des Nations
Monday evening deeply impressed an audience of 1,200 from United
Nations agencies and missions of more than 150 countries.
</P>
<P>
Before the beginning of the performance, Pierre Pelou, chairman
of the art committee of the United Nations Office at Geneva
(UNOG), welcomed the artists of the Chinese Tibetan Song and Dance
Ensemble (CTSDE) and said their performance was a precious gift to
the U.N. by the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The performance will contribute to world peace and promote
mutual understanding between the Chinese people and people from
other parts of the world, Pelou added.
</P>
<P>
CTSDE Director Tenzin thanked the UNOG for their efforts in
helping provide the Tibetan artists with the opportunity to
perform in the Palais des Nations.
</P>
<P>
He said the CTSDE's tour abroad showed that the Chinese
government has always attached great importance to protecting and
developing Tibet's traditional culture, which represents not only
part of the Chinese culture, but also a rare part of the cultural
heritage of all mankind.
</P>
<P>
The CTSDE artists arrived in Bern, Switzerland, on August 16
after a visit to Italy. The performance in the UNOG assembly hall
of the Palais des Nations was the first of their series of
scheduled performances in the country.
</P>
<P>
The CTSDE delegation, consisting of around 30 artists, left
here today for the western city of Fribourg to attend a week-long
International Re-Encounter of Folklore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
