<HEADLINE> Another UN Team of Missile Experts Arrives in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A U.N. team of experts in
self-propelled missiles arrived in Baghdad Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is the second team of its kind to visit Iraq in a week,
with a mission different from that of the previous one that has been
in Iraq since August 11.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Special Commission has been sending teams of experts to
Iraq to search for banned missiles and weapons of mass destruction
under U.N. resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi authorities have claimed that they have implemented the
U.N. resolutions and destroyed all those banned weapons, thus
demanding a quick lift of U.N. sanctions imposed on it after it
invaded Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
There had been confrontations between the U.N. teams and the
Iraqi authorities on the sites of inspections before. But no
problem has arisen between Iraqi authorities and the U.N. arms
inspectors since Richard Butler became chairman of the U.N. Special
Commission on Iraq last July.
</P>
<P>
Iraq affirms it will continue to cooperate with the
U.N. Special Commission, provided that the latter will do its
duties objectively, finish its mission as soon as possible and
recommend lifting the U.N. embargo on Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
