<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Holds Talks with Afghan Northern Warlords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 19 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary General's Special
Representative on Afghanistan Lakhdar Brahimi today held extensive
talks with the leaders of Afghan northern alliance in
Mazar-e-Sharif, about 300 km north of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi, who is on a two-week mission to assess the Afghan
situation and the UN peace efforts in Afghanistan, listened to the
views of the anti-Taliban alliance on the restoration of durable
peace in the war-hit country, official sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian diplomat, who last week held a detailed meeting
with the Taliban leaders in Kandahar, a major city in southern
Afghanistan, was accompanied by Head of the UN Special Mission on
Afghanistan, Norbert Holl, in the talks, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
However, the details of these talks were not available at the
moment, they said.
</P>
<P>
As part of his mission to consult the relevant countries in the
region on Afghanistan, the 63-year-old Brahimi will proceed late
in the day from Mazar-e-Sharif to Central Asian Republics, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban, who control the capital of Kabul and two thirds of
the Afghan territory, have set the release of their prisoners of
war held in Mazar-e-Sharif as a precondition for peace talks with
the northern alliance while the alliance has insisted the
formation of a joint political commission to demilitarize Kabul
and materialize a broad-based government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
