<HEADLINE> Good Prediction of Audience for Sydney 2000 Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A survey released on Tuesday
predicted a fine number of audience for the Sydney Olympics Games,
which is to be held from September 15 to October 1, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that 73 percent of Sydney residents planed to
present themselves on the Games and 31 percent of non-Sydney
respondents would travel to the Australia's largest city to watch
events.
</P>
<P>
Nation-wide 1,500 people responsed to the poll, which also
found that about one-third of people living outside the New South
Wales state capital intended to come in person to see the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
People who didn't plan to attend the Games were worried about
overcrowding. The poll showed that only 18 percent of non-Sydney
respondents will book hotels. Most said they would stay with
relatives or friends, and over 40 percent of Sydney respondents
were ready to host friends or relatives during the Games. 
</P>
