<HEADLINE> EU Industrial Production Up 1.1 Percent in March-May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's industrial
production grew 1.1 percent in the March-May period, with Spain
and Italy contributing much to the slight increase, Eurostat
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The growth was compared with the previous three months.
</P>
<P>
Latest Eurostat statistics showed that 10 of the 11 EU
countries of which figures are available have registered positive
growths while Britain was the only one to have posted a negative
growth of 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Following Spain and Italy were Finland, Belgium and France, all
at a growth rate of 1.2 percent while Denmark and the Netherlands
scored growths at 0.8 percent, followed by Germany and Greece at
0.7 percent and 0.2 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Motor vehicle manufacturing led the overall industrial growth
with an increase of 3.0 percent. 
</P>
