<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Agriculture Grows Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' agriculture
sector posted a 3.43 percent growth during the first half this
year, Agriculture Secretary Salvador Escudero said today.
</P>
<P>
Gross value of agricultural production was estimated at 250.2
billion pesos (8.4 billion U.S. dollars) at current prices, a 4.8
percent increase over the 1996 level, Escudero said in a report
sent to President Fidel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
Among the four subsectors, the poultry subsector registered the
highest growth rate of 10 percent, with its gross value of
production rising 19 percent from last year's level to hit 30.8
billion pesos (1 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The crop subsector generated 2.5 percent more output this year,
with its gross value of production rising 1.6 percent to 138.3
billion pesos (4.6 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The livestock subsector recorded a 5.4 percent growth, with its
gross receipts reaching 40.8 billion pesos (1.4 billion dollars)
or 10.7 percent higher than the 1996 level.
</P>
<P>
The fishery subsector managed to recover from last year's
negative growth as it inched up by 0.64 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
