<HEADLINE> Thai Government Slashes Budget by 59 Billion Baht </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet today formally
decided to cut its budget for the 1998 fiscal year by 59 billion
baht (about 2 billion u.s. dollars), local media reported.
</P>
<P>
The cut was made in a bid to meet the requirement of the
International Monetary Fund (IMF), which is on the way to provide
a huge financial rescue funding package to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The budget slashing was also made on the base that the
country's economic growth will be at three percent this year, and
the current account deficit will be no more than three percent of
the gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Thailand previously set the 1998 national budget at 982 billion
baht (32.7 billion dollars). officials from the budget bureau said
that the cut will not affect the country's economic growth as it
will mainly fall on consumer spending.  
</P>
</TEXT>
