<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourism Earns More Foreign Exchange for Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's tourism has registered
an increase in foreign exchange earnings and improvement in
facilities in recent years.
</P>
<P>
While foreign exchange earnings from tourism in the fiscal year
1994-95 stood at about 157 million U.S. dollars, this figure rose
by 6.1 percent to 167 million dollars in the following fiscal
year, said the Economic Survey for Fiscal Year 1996-97 issued by
the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
During the first eight months of the 1996-97 fiscal year which
ended on July 14, the tourism has netted in 96 million dollars,
the survey said.
</P>
<P>
As of mid-January 1996, the total number of hotels across Nepal
was 520 with 21,807 beds, including 72 star hotels and 448
non-star hotels.
</P>
<P>
This figure has rose to 632 vs 25,638 one year later, with star
and non-star hotels standing at 79 and 553 respectively, the
survey said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal is now trying its utmost to get ready for the Visit Nepal
Year '98 in order to further promote the tourism, one of its major
sources of foreign exchange.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
