<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Coastal Enterprises Change Operation Mechanism (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The provincial government of northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province in 1991 started to promote a "brand-name strategy" among
the local enterprises, the article said, and in the years since,
an overwhelming majority of provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions across the country have followed suit.
</P>
<P>
It gave two examples: the "Little Swan" washing machine and the
"China" and "Great Wall" brand pencils.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1979 in Wuxi, east China's Jiangsu Province, the
Little Swan Holdings Ltd. has developed rapidly into the country's
largest producer of fully automatic washing machines.
</P>
<P>
The article said that this is because the company has always
placed much emphasis on the buildup of its brand-name and worked
to upgrade its equipment, technology and management system.
</P>
<P>
It said that the "Little Swan" washing machine has for six
consecutive years enjoyed a market share higher than 40 percent,
and has been exported to more than 30 foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the Shanghai-based China No.1 Pencil Holdings
Ltd., producer of the nationwide famous "China" and "Great Wall"
brand pencils, shares similar experience with the Little Swan
company.
</P>
<P>
"Over the past four years, the pencil company has managed to
develop its products from the original four categories and 103
kinds to today's nine categories and 258 kinds," it said. "It
presented over 60 new products in 1996 alone."
</P>
<P>
To date, the article said, the annual profit of China No.1
Pencil Holdings Ltd. accounts for some 95 percent of the total
profits of all other pencil producers in the country.
</P>
<P>
It went on to say that another important factor in the change
of the operations system for enterprises is to continually exploit
the market in accordance with the characteristics of their own
products.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the Pearl River Piano Group based in Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, formed several years
ago a "Pearl River piano management and sales community," through
which it established trade connections with over 130 sales units
across the country.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, the group also managed to set up over 80
sales outlets in northern, northeastern, northwestern and eastern
China, where its sales record used to be very poor," the article
said. "Now the group can sell more than 15,000 pianos in these
regions each year."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
