<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Higher In Choppy Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
finished the day slightly higher in line with an improvement in
Wall Street, but off its highs after afternoon selling erased
morning gains.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index finished up 2.4 points at 2620.9 after
peaking at 2642.5 mid-morning.
</P>
<P>
Stock brokers said the tone of the market was hesitant ahead of
a meeting on interest rates at the Federal Reserve tonight.
</P>
<P>
Overnight, the Dow Jones industrial average closed 108.7 points
higher, after Friday's 247-point plunge.
</P>
<P>
Locally the all industrials index closed up 12.5 points at
4221.8, while the all resources index fell 6.5 to 1372.1 points.
</P>
<P>
Market leader BHP finished up 2.2 cents at 17.13 Australian
dollars, while News Corp. closed up three cents at 5.95 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The banking index, after earlier breaking through the 5000
barrier, closed only 3.8 points up at 4955.5.
</P>
<P>
Among other major industrials coca Cola Amatil surged 39.5 to
15.10 Australian dollars while transport giant Brambles shot up 20
cents at 27.90 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index closed down one cent at 1312.3 with the spot
gold price trading down 1.6 at 327.1 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 270.75 million shares traded valued
at 641.20 million Australian dollars (470.64 million U.S. dollars)
with rises outnumbering falls 577 to 469.  
</P>
</TEXT>
