<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Notice To Stop Unreasonable Fees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Finance has
recently issued a notice urging financial departments at all
levels to stop random fees, fines and apportions targeting the
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The work should be done in combination with the effort to
rectify the financial and economic order," the notice said.
</P>
<P>
The financial departments should work together with other
relevant departments to strictly examine the fees and fines
collected by governments at all levels and their subordinate
agencies, by administrative and government institutions, and by
social groups, the notice urged. Funds set up by them should also
be examined, it added.
</P>
<P>
All the fees and fines banned by the central government must be
canceled and made known to the public that they have been
canceled, it noted, adding that those unreasonable items that
evidently add to the financial burden of enterprises must be
resolutely revoked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
