<HEADLINE> Congress in Algebra, Combinatorics Held in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- More than 350 eminent
mathematicians from all over the world are participating in the
International Congress in Algebra and Combinatorics which opened
here today.
</P>
<P>
The congress is organized by the Southeast Asian Mathematical
Society and co-sponsored by the Chinese University of Hong Kong in
celebration of the 100th anniversary of the International
Mathematical Union.
</P>
<P>
The congress aims to promote research interest in algebra and
combinatorics in China and Far East Asian countries. Participants
will explore the application of algebra and combinatorics,
particularly in the design of high speed computers and the
electronic transmission of message.
</P>
<P>
The world's leading mathematicians from about two dozen
countries have come to attend the congress. Some 100 scholars from
China's mainland are also among them.
</P>
<P>
The congress will run through August 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
