<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Business Donates to Project Hope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A US business has donated one
million yuan (120,000 US dollars), to Project Hope in Changsha,
capital of central-south China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Xiong's Group, from the United States of America, has given a
donation worth of at least 100 million yuan to China's relatively
poor areas.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Delong, president of the group, has a special interest in
helping China's education. He financed 38 local colleges, middle
schools, primary schools and kindergartens in rural China.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, Xiong promised to send 100 county-level officials
to study in the United States.
</P>
<P>
After he got information about the backward conditions of rural
education in Hunan Province, Xiong, also president of the Fund of
Chinese Abroad Students in the US, decided to build two "Hope
Project" schools in the autonomous prefectures of Tujia and Miao
ethnic groups, in western Hunan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
