<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 12:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egyptian Office in PNA to be Relocated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Representation Office in
the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) in the self-ruled Gaza
will be moved to another "more spacious seat," the Middle East
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The movement is due to the "huge amount of work done and the
important Egyptian role in Palestinian self-rule areas," said
Mahmoud Karim, Egypt's representative to the PNA.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian official said Cairo's role is vital in Palestinian
self-rule areas but he did not say where the new office will be
located.
</P>
<P>
Karim, who is currently here, said new representation offices
for Japan, Chile and Oman will be inaugurated soon in the
Palestinian-controlled land.
</P>
<P>
Morocco, Qatar, Jordan, Tunisia, Norway, Germany, India, South
Africa, Denmark and Russia have already had representation offices
in the Palestinian self-rule areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
Consuls of France, the U.S., Britain, and Turkey in Israel
represent their governments to the PNA, he explained.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has been a key mediator in the Palestinian-Israeli peace
talks that initiated since 1991. Its first representation office
was inaugurated in Gaza in January l995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
