<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trade Deficit Down in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The balance of trade in goods
deficit in the Philippines dropped by 6.9 percent to 5.63 billion
U.S. dollars from 6.05 billion dollars during the first half of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Data released today by the National Statistics Office showed
that during the period, the merchandise trade between the
Philippines and the rest of the world expanded by 15.2 percent to
29.03 billion dollars from 25.21 billion dollars a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Imports rose by 10.9 percent to 17.33 billion dollars from last
year's 15.63 billion dollars while exports grew by 22.1 percent to
11.7 billion dollars from 9.58 billion dollars, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
The data also showed for June 1997 alone, total trade value
went up by 13.7 percent to 5.16 billion dollars from 4.54 billion
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit for the month continued to decline for the
fourth straight month as it settled at 906 million dollars, down
by 5.3 percent from the year-ago figure of 957 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
