<HEADLINE> Malaysia Considers Financing Commonwealth Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Foreign Minister
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said today his country will consider making
financial contribution to set up an office in New York for small
Commonwealth countries.
</P>
<P>
The cost for the office is estimated at 600,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"We will consider the amount to contribute for the purpose," he
told reporters after meeting visiting Commonwealth
Secretary-General Chief Emeka Anyaoku here.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Badawi said any Commonwealth country which had the
financial resources should contribute their bit as smaller
countries were also part of the Commonwealth family.
</P>
<P>
Anyaoku is paying a five-day visit to Malaysia as part of
preparations for the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting
(CHOGM) in Edinburgh, Scotland in October this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
