<HEADLINE> Indo-Nepal Foreign Secretary-Level Talks Review Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The foreign secretaries of
India and Nepal met here today to review the whole gamut of
bilateral relations between the two neighbors, Press Trust of
India reported.
</P>
<P>
The two-day foreign secretary-level talks will cover the
Indo-Nepal treaty of peace and friendship and issues relating to
trade and water resources.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Secretary K. Raghunath is heading the Indian delegation
while the Nepalese side is being led by Foreign Secretary Kumar
Gwayali.
</P>
<P>
The decision to hold foreign secretary-level talks was taken
during Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral's official visit to Nepal
in June last. 
</P>
</TEXT>
