<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Direct-Selling Group Opens Firm in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The U.S.-based
direct-selling group, Amway Corporation, has opened for business in
South Africa, forecasting turnover of more than 14.89 million
U.S. Dollars in its first year of operation.
</P>
<P>
Local daily Business Day today quoted Amway's South Africa
General Manager Peter Beaumont as saying that the group's initial
efforts in the country would focus on creating business
opportunities for individuals across a broad spectrum of the
population through its distributor network.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 10,000 South Africans were expected to join the
groups's international distribution force of more than 2.5
million Dollars in the first financial year.
</P>
<P>
"All South Africans will have the opportunity to get involved
in the Amway business, through which individuals can establish
their own independently run businesses without major capital
outlays," Beaumont said.
</P>
<P>
The launch into South Africa would create the first
opportunity for local citizens to become Amway distributors of
the U.S. manufacturers consumer products on a one-to-one basis,
marking the first Amway affiliate on the African continent, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
