<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore PM Cross-Examined in Defamation Suit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong was cross-examined in the High Court today for three
hours by Mr. George Carman, the Queens Counsel hired by Workers'
Party chief J.B. Jeyaretnam, who is being sued by government
leaders for defamation.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Carman suggested that Mr. Goh and ruling People's Action
Party (PAP) leaders had started legal action against Workers'
Party Secretary General Mr. Jeyaretnam to bankrupt him and keep
him out of Parliament, according to a local television report.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Goh said this was not true as Mr. Jeyaretnam was no threat
to the PAP and to himself. He also said he had been prepared to be
magnanimous towards Mr. Jeyaretnam during the out-of-court
discussions, which took place on Monday. However, no details of
the discussions can be revealed in court.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Carman also questioned Mr. Goh on his views of democracy
and why Mr. Goh said he was being magnanimous when he had asked
for substantial damages.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Goh replied that when his integrity as a leader has been
attacked he had to stand up and protect it.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Goh said the police report filed by Mr. Tang Liang Hong has
accused the Prime Minister of being a liar and of criminal
conspiracy. He said that it was like a Molotov cocktail and Mr.
Tang had given it to Mr. Jeyaretnam to hurl at the Prime Minister
at a critical time.
</P>
<P>
Goh said if politicians and ministers in Singapore do not
protect their integrity, they would be finished.
</P>
<P>
The PAP leaders, including Prime Minister Goh and Senior
Minister Lee Kuan Yew, are suing Mr. Jeyaretnam for telling a
Workers' Party election campaign rally on January 1 this year that
his team-mate in the Cheng San Group Representation Constituency,
lawyer Tang Liang Hong, had just placed before him two reports
the latter made to the police against the Prime Minister and his
team.
</P>
<P>
The PAP leaders claimed the words Jeyaretnam used implied that
they had conspired to commit criminal defamation against Mr. Tang
by labeling him an anti-Christian, anti-English educated Chinese
chauvinist.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
