<HEADLINE> Hungary Cracks Biggest Drug Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian police have cracked a
drug ring in the country's biggest drug trafficking case,
arresting all 24 members of the drug cartel, media reports said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The ring, whose chieftain is a Dutch living in Hungary, has
trafficked more than one ton hard drugs to Hungary over the past
one and half years, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
