<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Bombard Puliyankulam Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops at
dawn today began to Bombard Puliyankulam town in the Northern
province held by Tamil rebels, according to military sources here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The sources said air force fighter planes provided air cover to
the advancing troops by targeting the artillery positions of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in Puliyankulam town,
about 200 kilometers north of the capital.
</P>
<P>
A Vavuniya based military source was quoted as saying this
morning that the town was just 500 meters ahead from the
advancing troops.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of the Jaya Sikuru (Sure of Victory) operation
was launched by the government troops on May 13 to open a key
supply line along a highway from the government-held town of
Vavuniya to Kilinochchi in Jaffna peninsula, which runs through
the rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting for a separate Tamil state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
