<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Demands Japan's Clarification on Senior Official's Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- China earnestly hopes that the
Japanese side will "refrain from doing anything again that amounts
to an interference in China's internal affairs or jeopardizes the
Sino-Japanese relations."
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang made the
remarks here today in response to a question on Japanese Chief
Cabinet Secretary Seiroku Kajiyama's statement concerning the
Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Kajiyama clearly indicated in a TV Asahi interview program on
August 17 that the so-called "surrounding areas" pertaining to the
scope of the Japanese-U.S. security cooperation should "naturally
include the Taiwan Straits."
</P>
<P>
Shen said that China is "seriously concerned" about the
above-mentioned remarks made by Seiroku Kajiyama, a chief member
of the Japanese Government, and asked the Japanese Government to
make "a clear-cut clarification" on Kajiyama's statement.
</P>
<P>
The position of the Chinese side on the issue of
Japanese-U.S. security cooperation is clear and consistent, Shen
said.
</P>
<P>
As is known to all, Shen pointed out, Taiwan is an inalienable
part of the Chinese territory, and the Taiwan question is purely
China's internal affairs. This has become a consensus of the
international community, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side has made solemn commitment on this in the
Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the Treaty of Peace and
Friendship Between China and Japan, said Shen, emphasizing that
"Japan should therefore strictly honor its commitment."
</P>
<P>
He said, "the Chinese side earnestly hopes that the Japanese
side will be consistent in words and deeds, and refrain from doing
anything again that amounts to an interference in China's internal
affairs or jeopardizes the Sino-Japanese relations."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
