<HEADLINE> Share Prices Almost Unchanged on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rose shortly
after opening but declined later on the Singapore market with the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index sliding by merely 0.32
point to close at 1,918.53 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 158.02 million units, valued
at 493.03 million Singapore dollars (about 326.51 million US
dollars). Declines led advances by 203 to 133, while 269 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 11.85 million units. It was followed by Asia Food &AMP;
Properties which had 10.71 million shares traded. Singapore
Technologies (ST) Aero was next with 8.17 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.2 dollars to finish at 24.2 Singapore
dollars. Malaya Banking increased by 60 cents to end at 11.6
Singapore dollars, while ST Aero closed 55 cents higher at 2.88
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Hume was the biggest loser as it declined by
5.02 dollars to end at 3.98 Singapore dollars. Local car
distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage fell by 60 cents to close at 11
Singapore dollars and property developer City Developments and
Creative 50 were 40 cents lower at 11 and 31.7 Singapore dollars
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
