<HEADLINE> SADC Ministers Meet on Trade Promotion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Ministers for industries
and trade from member states of the Southern African Development
Community (SADC) will begin their meeting here on Monday to
discuss on trade promotion in the region.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to adopt an agenda to harmonize
customs tarrif in the region by the year 2004 and discuss a
proposal to end the Lome IV agreement in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Participants include delegates from Mauritius, Malawi,
Lesotho, Zimbabwe, Botswana, Swaziland, Namibia, Zambia, South
Africa and Tanzania, with Angola not represented. 
</P>
