</P>
<P>
-- The decision by the government of Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
to use a part of defense spending to finance job creation has
aroused strong criticism from the center-right opposition and
unions. The reduction of defense spending could be the first subject
of confrontation between the government and President Jacques
Chirac, who has promised to ``see to it that our armed forces
continue to have at their disposal the necessary resources for their
renovation, maintenance of capacities and their training.''
