<HEADLINE> First Upholstery School to Be Opened in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The first school for design,
upholstery and interior decoration in Zambia will be opened here
soon, it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
Jonathan Mukunta, designer and supervisor of Crimargo, a
Yugoslavian company in Zambia, said Zambia has all the natural
resources to make a variety of products.
</P>
<P>
The training of young people in design, upholstery and
decoration will help combat unemployment in the country, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
Young people should be given a chance to learn skills to
exploit these inputs, Mukunta added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the company is also making efforts to promote
products from Kangonga production center in Ndola, northern
Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Handicrafts and other locally-made products such as armchairs,
dining chairs, tables, cocktail chairs and garden chairs are
ordered from the center run by the blind.
</P>
<P>
Crimargo has been promoting African designs since it was set
up in 1996 in Lusaka. 
