<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Rockets Northern Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 19 (Xinhua) -- In a major escalation of
clashes in South Lebanon, Hezbollah forces fired 45 rounds of
Katyusha rockets into northern Israel today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by Israeli Army said the rocket attack came
about early in the morning, and the rockets hit its northern
border town Kiryat Shimona and other places near the northern part
of the Lake Kinneret (or Sea of Galilee).
</P>
<P>
The army said there were low casualties in the attack,
although no exact figures were available at this time.
</P>
<P>
It added that the anti-Israeli Hezbollah forces had claimed
responsibility for the attack, which is the most serious since
Israel and Hezbollah forces reached ceasefire in April last year
after Israel's Operation Grapes of Wrath.
</P>
<P>
Today's Hezbollah attack was apparently an revenge operation
for the Monday's shelling of the southern Lebanese town Sidon by
the pro-Israeli South Lebanese Army (SLA), which killed six
Lebanese civilians and wounded 36 others.
</P>
<P>
The SLA shelling was reportedly the revenge attack for the
death of two teenager children of a late SLA commander, who were
killed in a roadside bombing planned by Hezbollah. Late Hezbollah
forces retaliated by shelling Jezzine, killing a 60-year-old man.
</P>
<P>
Monday's civilian fatalities were the highest since the
Operation Grapes of Wrath. Both Israel and Lebanon had submitted
complaints to the five-nation committee monitoring the ceasefire
understanding, which barred both sides from attacking civilians.
</P>
<P>
Israel on Monday moved quickly to distance itself from the
latest clashes between SLA and Hezbollah forces. Criticizing the
shelling on Sidon, Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai expressed
"the deepest regret over the attack on innocent civilians,"
saying it was totally against Israel's policy.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai told reporters in Haifa that Israel had conveyed
messages to the Lebanese Army and other parties in the conflict in
an attempt to prevent an escalation. He said Israel had no
interests in a deterioration of the situation, but had every
interest in stabilizing it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
