<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 8 GMT August 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The Teamsters union and United Parcel Service
(UPS) reached a tentative agreement Tuesday to end a 15-day strike
that disrupted package deliveries nationwide, the Associated Press
(AP) reported. The settlement followed more than 80 hours of
talks since Thursday, with pressure from Labor Secretary Alexis
Herman and some prodding from President Bill
Clinton.(UPS-Agreement)
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Ukrainian Foreign Minister Gennady Udovenko says he
will actively boost United Nations reforms during his tenure as
the president of the 52nd U.N. General Assembly. Udovenko told the
Russian Interfax news agency that U.N. reforms should, firstly,
focus on strengthening its role in handling a range of priority
issues, such as peace, security and disarmament as well as
economic, social, humanitarian, ecological and human rights
issues.(Ukraine-Foreign Minister-UN)
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian "Progress M-35" cargo ship redocked
successfully with Mir space station Tuesday at 4:52 p.m. local
time, the Itar TASS news agency reported. The redocking was
conducted by Russian cosmonaut Vladimir Solovyov and Pavel
Vinogradov through remote control.The cargo ship left Mir space
station and had been flying in space for 12 days in order that the
24th manned shuttle could dock with the Mir.(Russia-Mir) 
</P>
