<HEADLINE> New Beijing Mobile Communications Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has opened a new GSM
network, or global mobile communications network, with a total
handling capacity of 400,000 mobil phones.
</P>
<P>
The new "138" network offers the same function and services as
the older "139" network, Beijing's first GSM network was
introduced in April 1995.
</P>
<P>
The latter network was approaching full handling capacity at
300,000 subscribers..
</P>
<P>
Mobile phones registered with Beijing Telecom provide direct
telephone access to 29 provinces and autonomous regions, as well
as numerous overseas country's regions, including Hong Kong and
Macao, and Singapore, Finland, and Germany. 
</P>
