<HEADLINE> Booming Border Trade in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lhasa, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Border trade has been flourishing
in the Tibet Autonomous Region, with deals totaling 500 million
yuan over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Border trade has been growing at an annual rate of 14 percent
since 1992, according to the Regional Department of Foreign Trade.
</P>
<P>
Some 138 companies, both collective and private, are currently
involved in border trade in Tibet. Major trade items include
textiles and light industrial products, as well as machinery,
electronic products, farm and sideline products, and animal
by-products.
</P>
<P>
Tibet's six trading ports and 28 border trade markets
provide local people with an opportunity to engage in trade
activities with people from neighboring countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
