<HEADLINE> Leading Officials Join No Smoking Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- A group of 138 leading officials
at the ministerial level from 49 central government departments
have signed a pledge to refrain from smoking in public places.
</P>
<P>
The officials are also advocating smoking prohibitions at
public events and social activities, and will ask their
aides and children not to smoke.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Smoking and Health Association, the
ranks of Chinese male smokers have swelled to over 300 million and
those of female smokers to 20 million, with tobacco threatening
the health of over 590 million Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
Central government departments launched a quit-smoking campaign
in May this year, with over 50 percent of ministry officials and 20
percent of ministerial level buildings now offering smoke-free
environments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
