<HEADLINE> Liaoning Exports More Machinery, Electronics Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province, one of the country's major heavy industrial bases,
recorded a 45 percent rise in exports of machinery and
electronic products for the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Exports of such machinery and products came to 990 million US
dollars during that period, according to the Liaoning provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
Government statistics show that foreign-funded enterprises
contributed nearly 69 percent of total exports.
</P>
<P>
Exports of the machinery and electronics products from the port
city of Dalian accounted for 70 percent of the provincial total in
the period.
</P>
<P>
Dandong, a city bordering the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) and the province's second largest exporter of
machinery and electronics products, exported 8.53 percent of
Liaoning's total exports. Dandong has replaced Shenyang,
the provincial capital, as Liaoning's second largest exporter.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electronics products manufactured in the province
are exported to 120 countries and regions, including the United
States, Japan and Southeast Asian countries, according to Xu
Zhaoshu, director of the Liaoning Provincial Machinery and
Electronic Products Import and Export Office.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that Liaoning plans to export machinery and
electronics products valued at two billion US dollars by the end
of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
