<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Delegation Visits Armenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YEREVAN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- China has made remarkable
progress in its reform and it is of help for Armenia to use the
experience of countries including China as reference in its own
development.
</P>
<P>
Babken Araktsyan, speaker of the National Assembly of the
Republic of Armenia, said this today to Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee Vice-Chairman Wang Bingqian who
heads a visiting delegation here.
</P>
<P>
The visit by the Chinese delegation "is another step forward in
Sino-Armenia relations" and will further close links between the
two countries' parliaments, said Araktsyan.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the two parliaments are faced with enormous
tasks and it is encouraging to see them willing to deepen their
contacts and cooperate in politics, economy, culture, science and
other areas.
</P>
<P>
Araktsyan also hoped the two countries would further develop
economic cooperation, saying there is great potential in this area.
</P>
<P>
Wang conveyed greetings to Araktsyan from Chinese NPC Standing
Committee Chairman Qiao Shi and said that Sino-Armenia relations
have been developing smoothly ever since the two countries
established diplomatic relations in 1992.
</P>
<P>
To develop friendly and cooperative ties between the two on the
basis of the five principles of peaceful co-existence will be
beneficial not only to the two peoples but also to world peace and
stability, he added.
</P>
<P>
China was glad to see broader exchanges in areas such as trade,
science and culture and closer ties between the two parliaments.
Wang also expressed his belief that Sino-Armenia relations would
enter a new stage because of the joint efforts of the two
governments.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting the two parliaments exchanged notes on
presenting 500,000 yuan (about 60,241 U.S. dollars) worth of
office equipment to the Armenian National Assembly by the Standing
Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the Armenian National Assembly, the
Chinese delegation arrived in the Armenian capital of Yerevan at
midday on an official goodwill visit. This is the first visit by a
high-ranking Chinese NPC delegation to Armenia. 
</P>
