<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Improve Measurement Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is stepping up its
efforts to create a national measurement center to better the
country's measurement work to help improve the quality of its
industrial products and strengthen its scientific research.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Science, Technology and Environment is speeding
up its work to set up the National Metrological Institute to
provide primary measurement standards and calibration services
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's industrial products represented an increasing share
of the country's export volume, so quality control to meet
international specifications has become crucial for Thailand,
officials from the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Accurate measurement is also vital to other activities like
scientific research and development, pollution control, medical
services, etc., they added.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers today said that Thailand lacks high-accuracy
measurement or calibration equipment and it has to send its
measurement instruments and equipment abroad for calibration,
which has resulted in unreliable measurements.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is reportedly planning to combine its metrological
service provided by its agencies, including the Science Service
Department and the Thailand Institute of Scientific and
Technological Research, and put it under the national measurement
center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
