<HEADLINE> Beijing Television Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Beijing manufacturers exported
slightly over 5,000 color television sets in the first six months
of this year, up 39.5 percent on last year's same period,
</P>
<P>
Figures from Beijing Customs show the city's manufacturers
exported a total of 25,000 TV sets, with state-owned enterprises
producing 97 percent of total export items.
</P>
<P>
Beijing exported 147,000 TV sets valued at 6.55 million US
dollars between Jan. 1995 and June 1997.
</P>
<P>
Recent reports indicate that the nationalization rate of 36-54
cm, colored TV tubes jumped from less than 50 percent in the early
1990s to 90 percent in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
