<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy to Overhaul Its Research System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Italy will thoroughly overhaul its
research system this year so as to meet the country's changing
industrial needs.
</P>
<P>
The shake-up stems from recognition that the present state of
Italian research is not sufficient for future industrial
development, the ANSA news agency today quoted University
Minister, Luigi Berlinguer, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Berlinguer, who is also minister for scientific research,
outlined his plans for the future of national research in a
special report to be considered by parliament.
</P>
<P>
The plans include setting-up of a new coordination center, the
creation of new bodies to oversee research work, new functions for
existing research centers and, most importantly, a reorganization
of financing to draw more cash from the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Berlinguer recognized the need for a research system which
would put Italy in line with other industrialized countries. It
would marry the politics of research and innovation to other
strategic state decisions, from questions of national security to
economic relations, ANSA said.
</P>
<P>
According to the plans, the new tendency would be towards
decentralization, with major autonomy for research bodies, a
redefinition and simplification of their roles accompanied by a
reduction in their numbers.
</P>
<P>
A new "committee for research and technology" (CRT), composed
of science experts from Italy and abroad, nominated by the prime
minister himself, would report directly to the prime minister and
the university minister.
</P>
<P>
Wider research targets and budgets would be under the control
of the government's existing Economic Planning Committee (CIPE),
Berlinguer said.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the Italian scientific and economic community
would provide a national consultancy network and it was hoped that
a "national assembly" would meet regularly to decide key issues
of policy and financing, ANSA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
