<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas-funded Firms Play Significant Role in China's Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- Customs statistics indicate
foreign trade by overseas-funded enterprises in the first half of
this year rose 15 percent from a year ago to reach 67.21 billion
US dollars, the "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounted for 46.7 percent of China's total foreign
trade volume in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Last year, these firms held 47.2 percent of China's foreign
trade totaling 289.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented processing trade continues to be the dominant
trade mode for these firms. Trade volume of this sector climbed
from 70.6 percent last year to 74.4 percent in the first half of
the year. Processing exports rose 24.4 percent to 28.13 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Processing imported materials is still the dominant form of
the processing trade, as 90.7 percent or 45.36 billion US dollars
of the processing trade during the period came from processing of
supplied materials.
</P>
<P>
General trade handled by overseas-funded enterprises jumped 32
percent from a year ago to 8.05 billion US dollars in the first
half of this year. General exports and imports surged 36.4 percent
and 27.3 percent to 4.34 billion US dollars and 3.71 billion US
dollars, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
