<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Cargo Ship Redocks With Mir Space Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian "Progress M-35" cargo
ship redocked successfully with Mir space station today at 4:52
p.m. local time, the Itar TASS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The redocking was conducted by Russian cosmonaut Vladimir
Solovyov and Pavel Vinogradov through remote control.
</P>
<P>
The cargo ship left Mir space station and had been flying in
space for 12 days in order that the 24th manned shuttle could dock
with the Mir.
</P>
<P>
The redocking was originally scheduled on last Sunday, but
failed because of computer problems. The station has been running
on about half power since the June 25 collision, when the power
cables were intentionally disconnected in order to seal off the
module.
</P>
<P>
The Progress M-35 cargo ship, which entered the orbit in July,
will carry the rubbish and leave the orbit as soon as it uses up
fuels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
