in Buenos Aires on August 13. Under the agreement, the two
countries will improve cooperation in electric power.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazil's international reserves reached a
record high of 63 billion U.S. dollars in August, Central Bank
official Francisco Lopez announced.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazil's state-owned telecom company,
Telebras, started its cellphone automatic service in some
Uruguayan cities on August 15. Telebras has also signed a similar
contract with Argentina, which will allow it to open services in
Buenos Aires.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Mutual investments between Argentina and
Brazil have reached 1.5 billion U.S. dollars, according to a
statement released by a spokesman of the business sector on August
12.
</P>
<P>
Argentine investors basically took risks in Brazil's petroleum
and food industries, while Brazilian entrepreneurs have had a
major interest in gas exploitation and automotive assembly plants
in Argentina. 
