<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Hits New Low Against US Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 19 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah hit
another low Monday surpassing the 3,000 level against the U.S.
dollar as share prices slumped 2.3 percent, local press today
quoted dealers here as saying.
</P>
<P>
Spot rupiah, which opened at 2,930/45, plunged to 3,005 at
midday trading before recovering to 2,970/2,995 at close.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah weakened against the dollar after the central bank
scrapped its intervention band last Thursday, effectively floating
the unit, on sustained speculative attacks on all regional
currencies.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah, which started the year at 2,363 to the dollar, had
fallen almost 27 percent by Monday, with further weakness seen
possible.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at the Jakarta Stock Exchange, share prices dropped
2.3 percent Monday, with composite index closing 19.928 points
lower at 597.778.
</P>
<P>
Stock dealers said the index dropped 35.187 points to 582.512
during the launch break after descending 49 points to 565.78 in
the morning session.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the fall to the unclear direction of the
rupiah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
