<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Troops Alert on Colombian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A number of Venezuelan soldiers
have been deployed to Apure, a state in western Venezuela
bordering Colombia, where a Venezuelan officer and a civilian were
kidnapped by a Colombian armed group.
</P>
<P>
Five helicopters, and Bronco and C-130 aircraft are ready to
take action against kidnappers in the district.
</P>
<P>
Officers of the Venezuelan security forces asked their
Colombian counterparts to take coordinated action to fight the
Colombian rebels.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, a small group of Venezuelan officials were
attacked by 15 Colombians in Chorrosquero seaport, Apure, when the
Venezuelan officials were traveling in a jeep.
</P>
<P>
No organized Colombian guerrillas have claimed. But Venezuelan
sides said the attack was perpetrated by the rebel National
Liberation Army of Colombia. 
</P>
