<HEADLINE> PSG Penalised for European Cup Mistake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Paris St Germain's European Cup
campaign suffered a major setback on Monday when UEFA penalised
them two goals for fielding a suspended player against Steaua
Bucharest in a preliminary round first leg match.
</P>
<P>
UEFA had altered the club's 3-2 defeat in Bucharest last week
to a 3-0 loss after ruling that defender Laurent Fournier was
ineligible.
</P>
<P>
Fournier, who played the whole match against Steaua, should not
have been on the pitch because of his bookings from last season.
</P>
<P>
The punishment meant that PSG will have to score at least three
goals in the return match in Paris on August 27 to have a hope of
progressing to extra time and a penalty shoot-out. 
