<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Shipping Group Founded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 19 (Xinhua) -- China's biggest shipping
conglomerate was set up on Monday in Shanghai, China's leading
port city.
</P>
<P>
the conglomerate, called "aircraft carrier", is composed of the
Shanghai Shipping Co., the Guangzhou Shipping Ltd., the Dalian
Shipping Co., the China Shipping International Marine Technology
Service Ltd. and Zhong Jiao Marine Industry, the "China Daily"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"It is a merger of China's strong shipping companies aimed at
reinforcing the nation's capability to compete with overseas
rivals," said Li Kelin, president of the new China Shipping
(Group) Co.
</P>
<P>
The new company, with combined assets of 25 billion yuan, has
413 big ships with 8.37 million deadweight tonnage. Its sales
reached 6.4 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
It ships 80 percent of the coal and 90 percent of petroleum to
China's coastal areas. Last year the group company transported 145
million tons of cargo and seven million passengers.
</P>
<P>
Its business ranges from ship repairs to trade, shipping
agents, telecommunications, real estate, fuel supply and training.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to have five big group companies in the
transportation sector. They include China Shipping, China
Oceangoing Co, Changjiang Shipping Co, China Road and Bridge Corp
and China Port Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
