Melbourne, Victoria, over the next seven years, as it launches a
new family car to take on the Ford Falcon and Holden Commodore,
the cars produced by Toyota's competitors in Australia.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- Australia must deregulate its labor market more if it wants
to see a big drop in unemployment, Ted Evans, Secretary of the
Federal Treasury, said yesterday. 
