<HEADLINE> Brazil Force Italy to Goalless Draw at Universiade Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Brazil forced hosts Italy
to a goalless draw at the opening match of the Universiade football
tournament at Trapani on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team, technically better but physically weaker
than their Italian opponents, survived ruthless attacks from the
Italian eleven, especially in the last 25 minutes, and held on to the
final whistle.
</P>
<P>
The first half was a even game as neither team could gain an upper
hand over the others. But as the Brazilians appeared tired in the
second half, the Italian team began to take advantage.
</P>
<P>
Though the Italian launched fierce attacks at the Brazilian
goal, their efforts were turned down by tough defence from the
Brazilians and at the same time, most of their shots were wide or high
into the sky and cast little threat to the Brazilian goal.
</P>
<P>
According to the official results issued by the organising
committee, China trounced Czech Republic 4-0 while the United States
beat Nigeria 3-0. China led group D with better goal difference
over the United States.
</P>
<P>
In a group C match played in Marsala, South Korea came twice
from one goal down to draw Uruguay 2-2. Japan beat Ireland 1-0 in
group B and Britain drew Iran 0-0 in a group A match.
</P>
<P>
The round-robin group competitions of football tournament will
have a rest day on Tuesday while the opening ceremony of the 19th
World University Games will be held at Palermo on Tuesday evening.
</P>
</TEXT>
