<HEADLINE> Russia, USA Sign Flight Safety Memorandum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 18 (Xinhua) -- American Boeing and the Russian
Federal Aviation Service (FAS) have signed a memorandum today on
intentions to ensure the flight safety and cooperate in the air
traffic control matters, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by FAS Deputy Director Viktor Galkin
from the Russian side and by Boeing Vice-President Charles Higgins
from the American side.
</P>
