<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0278 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> VW Group Profits Up 73 Percent in First Half-Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Volkswagen group today
said that its first-half profits this year soared to some 488
million marks (268 million U.S. dollars), up 73 percent over the
same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Its sales during the first six months this year increased by 12
percent to 56.5 billion marks (31.0 billion dollars), Europe's
largest car maker reported from its headquarters in Wolfsburg.
</P>
<P>
The group owed most of the profits to rising exports or sales
from overseas plants, according to it.
</P>
<P>
Volkswagen produced nearly 2.2 million cars through June this
year, up 9.9 percent from the level a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that some 1.7 million of the cars were destined
for non-German markets, up 13.9 percent, while domestic demand was
down slightly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
