<DOCNO> XIE19970819.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik Government Settles Conflict by Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Tajik government is now
oriented toward resolving the conflict by force because its peace
initiatives have proved unsuccessful, Tajik presidential spokesman
Zafar Saidov stated today in Dushanbe.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik government forces today launched a new offensive on
the positions of Mutinous colonel Makhmud Khudoiberdyev and seized
a strategic bridge in the area of Garavuti, according to a report
reaching here from Dushanbe, Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
In the fierce battle for the bridge, government forces hit five
units of the enemy's armored equipment, destroyed three
antiaircraft installations and one howitzer.
</P>
<P>
According to the information of the Defense Ministry, 50 armed
rebels were killed, while three men were killed and 10 wounded
from the government forces.
</P>
<P>
It was said about ten pieces of armored equipment and an
anti-aircraft gun of the rebellious brigade were damaged in the
fighting.
</P>
<P>
The government forces are continuing the operation to blockade
the brigade under Khudoiberdiyev near the town of Kabodian, 200
Kilometers away from Dushanbe.
</P>
<P>
Report said that Khudoiberdyev is strong enough to put up
resistance. He continues to receive considerable aid from abroad.
His Supporters are continuing to defect to the presidential side.
About 150-160 people remain faithful to Khudoiberdiyev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
